eedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mcp1665702712185.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mcp1665702712185.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mcp1665702712185.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mcp1665702712185\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                \n Display Format\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify a display format for field layout, which can be used to format the data for display or string substitution.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__topic_d7676e1_d7677e1_d7678e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__p_d7679e1_d7680e1_d7681e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS (</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Format</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For Numeric, Float, Date, Time, or Datetime, you can specify an NLS format:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__p_d7682e1_d7683e1_d7684e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS (</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$NLS (</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">NlsFormat</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">))</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__section_w3ab1b5b3_w4ab1b5_w5ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__p_d7685e1_d7686e1_d7687e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS(True/False)</code> for Boolean data where the actual values are 1 and 0</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__section_w6ab1b5b5_w7ab1b5_w8ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__p_d7688e1_d7689e1_d7690e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS(AA*, dd-MMM*-yyyy)</code> for a Date field</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__section_w9ab1b5b7_w10ab1b5_w11ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__table_d704e1_d705e1_d706e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Technical Name:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">FORMAT</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Expected Value:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">String of up to 32 characters. Supports Unicode.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Default Value:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__section_mj4_g53_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d653895e163\">Arguments</h2>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__section_ah4_h53_5cc\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e17\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Argument</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Format</var>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Code or pattern that defines the\n\t\t\t\t\t formatting applied to the data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The available display formats depend on the data type. For more information, see:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e66\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wnj1665702551652.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wnj1665702551652.html\" title=\"When defining the layout of fields with data type Boolean, you can specify the value to be displayed.\">Display Formats for Boolean Data</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e71\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rio1665702551730.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rio1665702551730.html\" title=\"When defining the layout of fields with data type String, it is possible, although not usual, to apply a display format.\">Display Formats for Strings</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e76\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ggh1665702551806.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ggh1665702551806.html\" title=\"Display formats for numeric data typically apply a pattern to the data. For example, you can define the number of digits before or after the decimal point, put a currency symbol in front (or behind the value), or define whether the decimal and thousand separators should be commas or periods.\">Display Formats for Numeric and Float Data</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e81\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gxf1665702551990.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gxf1665702551990.html\" title=\"Display formats for date and time data typically apply a pattern to the data. For example, you can indicate whether you want a short form of the date or a long form, and whether to use space, slashes, or dashes as separators.\">Display Formats for Date and Time Data</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">NlsFormat</var>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mcp1665702712185__d6161e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Keyword or display format pattern that\n\t\t\t\t\t defines the NLS formatting to be applied to the data; one of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NLS(NUMBER)</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NLS(FLOAT)</span> or<code class=\"ph codeph\"> $NLS(<var class=\"keyword varname\">Format</var>)</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">By default, if <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NLS_LOCALE</span> is specified in the assignment file, or in ProcScript (using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlslocale</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$webinfo(\"locale\")</span>), the language and styling conventions of the locale are applied. You can override this default behavior using <code class=\"ph codeph\">$NLS(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">NlsFormat</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wkb1665702552218.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wkb1665702552218.html\" title=\"For Numeric, Float, Date, Time, and DateTime data, the formatting rules that are applied depend on the NLS settings.\">NLS Display Formats</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__section_tvh_k53_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d653895e345\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__p_d7697e1_d7698e1_d7699e1\">Display formats apply a pattern to the data to control\n            how it is formatted for display. They can be specified in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field\n               Layout</span> property, and can also be controlled using the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$format</span> ProcScript function.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__p_d7700e1_d7701e1_d7702e1\">For Numeric, Float, Date, Time, or Datetime fields, you\n            can browse for a prefedined display format.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__p_d7703e1_d7704e1_d7705e1\">The available display formats depend on the data type.\n            For more information, see:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__ul_hpc_l53_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__li_d3728e1_d3729e1_d3730e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wnj1665702551652.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wnj1665702551652.html\" title=\"When defining the layout of fields with data type Boolean, you can specify the value to be displayed.\">Display Formats for Boolean Data</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__li_d3731e1_d3732e1_d3733e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rio1665702551730.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rio1665702551730.html\" title=\"When defining the layout of fields with data type String, it is possible, although not usual, to apply a display format.\">Display Formats for Strings</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__li_d3734e1_d3735e1_d3736e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ggh1665702551806.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ggh1665702551806.html\" title=\"Display formats for numeric data typically apply a pattern to the data. For example, you can define the number of digits before or after the decimal point, put a currency symbol in front (or behind the value), or define whether the decimal and thousand separators should be commas or periods.\">Display Formats for Numeric and Float Data</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__li_d3737e1_d3738e1_d3739e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gxf1665702551990.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gxf1665702551990.html\" title=\"Display formats for date and time data typically apply a pattern to the data. For example, you can indicate whether you want a short form of the date or a long form, and whether to use space, slashes, or dashes as separators.\">Display Formats for Date and Time Data</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__section_s43_m53_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d653895e405\">Applies to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__ul_czt_n53_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__li_d3710e1_d3711e1_d3712e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lpv1665702557117.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpv1665702557117.html\" title=\"Property that specifies how the field's data is formatted for display. The value can be a comma-separated list of shorthand codes, or a reference to a modeled field layout.\">Field Layout</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mcp1665702712185__li_d3713e1_d3714e1_d3715e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ijx1665702711766.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ijx1665702711766.html\" title=\"A Modeled Field Layout is a Development Object that defines the way data is displayed.\">Modeled Field Layout</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iha1665702711837.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Field Layout Codes</a><p>Field layout codes specify how data is formatted for display. When multiple codes are specified, they must be separated by commas.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/spf1665703007836.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$format</a><p>Return the field data, formatted according to the display format (DIS).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fjz1665702531973.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Language and Locale</a><p>The language of an application is associated not only with a character set, but with regional conventions for sorting, for expressing numbers, currency, date and time, and so on. The combination of language and region is known as locale.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529841\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529841\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Display Format Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Display Format Specify a display format for field layout, which can be used to format the data for display or string substitution. DIS ( Format ) For Numeric, Float, Date, Time, or Datetime, you can specify an NLS format: DIS ( $NLS ( NlsFormat )) Example: DIS(True/False) for Boolean data where the actual values are 1 and 0 Example: DIS(AA*, dd-MMM*-yyyy) for a Date field Technical Name: FORMAT Expected Value: String of up to 32 characters. Supports Unicode. Default Value: None Arguments Argument Description Format Code or pattern that defines the formatting applied to the data. The available display formats depend on the data type. For more information, see: Display Formats for Boolean Data Display Formats for Strings Display Formats for Numeric and Float Data Display Formats for Date and Time Data NlsFormat Keyword or display format pattern that defines the NLS formatting to be applied to the data; one of $NLS(NUMBER) , $NLS(FLOAT) or $NLS( Format ) . By default, if $NLS_LOCALE is specified in the assignment file, or in ProcScript (using $nlslocale and $webinfo(\"locale\") ), the language and styling conventions of the locale are applied. You can override this default behavior using $NLS( NlsFormat ) . For more information, see NLS Display Formats . Description Display formats apply a pattern to the data to control how it is formatted for display. They can be specified in the Field Layout property, and can also be controlled using the $format ProcScript function. For Numeric, Float, Date, Time, or Datetime fields, you can browse for a prefedined display format. The available display formats depend on the data type. For more information, see: Display Formats for Boolean Data Display Formats for Strings Display Formats for Numeric and Float Data Display Formats for Date and Time Data Applies to Field Layout Modeled Field Layout Related Links Field Layout Codes Field layout codes specify how data is formatted for display. When multiple codes are specified, they must be separated by commas. $format Return the field data, formatted according to the display format (DIS). Language and Locale The language of an application is associated not only with a character set, but with regional conventions for sorting, for expressing numbers, currency, date and time, and so on. The combination of language and region is known as locale. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}